Actress Ufuoma McDermott has shared viable lessons noteworthy from her colleague, Rita Dominic’s star-studded wedding. Tuesday was a day of grand celebration for Rita Dominic, as she tied the knot with the publisher of Daily Times, Fidelis Anosike, in Owerri, Imo State. Social media was thrown into frenzy as Nollywood stars stormed Owerri to share in her joy. Beautiful photos and videos from the events were shared online by many celebrities who attended the joyous occasion and those who also couldn’t. Many were indeed felicitous with the movie star’s wedding as they had several complimentary remarks for her while wishing her marriage bliss. 		 			Celebrities that have announced pregnancies in 2022		 		 		 			Jesus, doctors transformed my body, says Tonto Dikeh		 		 		 			Timi Dakolo announces collaboration with Davido		 		 Reacting, Ufuoma McDermott in a post on her Instagram page said Rita Dominic’s wedding indeed spread happiness to all and sundry. McDermott also urged people to sustain their happiness and keep spreading love to others. “Don’t lie o! How many of you could literally taste the happiness from Riri’s wedding yesterday???? Gosh! I just love sha. This proves that we need love to make the world better”, she wrote. “We all felt it. For a moment, we forgot about the worries and pressures of life. Our hearts were transported to a happy place. Let’s keep the momentum and spread more love.”